Steven Wilson hopes the album will be a gateway to possible new fans
Why did you launch your new Transience compilation on vinyl?
This was originally conceived as an idea for Disk Shop Day, but I missed the opportunity.
My record house had suggested collecting some of my shortest and most accessible songs.
I became easily obsessed with the idea of doing something like "introduction into Steven Wilson's music" and I necessarily kept the project being launched only on the vinyl.
Whoever buys the vinyl also receives a downloaded variant at high resolution.
Are you worried that the album won't show your music in her real light?
