There is a lot of progressive rock that focuses rather on technical complexity than on the musical side.
Pink Floyd, the most famous progressive rock band of all time, has passed the time test because they have always put emphasis on the music and the atmosphere.
What are you preparing for Albert Hall shows?
I don't want to reveal too much.
The repertoire will be completely different every night.
In the first, it will be a version of the Hand. Erase show that I had this year, but on steroids, with a few guests.
The second night will be rather an incursion into my history, being more oriented towards the fans who have followed me over the years.
How did you choose Matt Berry to open your show the second night?
And me and the others on the tour team are big fans of [the comedy show on Channel 4] Toast of London, to the point where we give all the time quoted from it.
I thought I'd listen to Matt's music too, so I bought his album, Music for Insomniacs.
