The Norwegian Institute for Public Health coordinated a study on the development of motors of children whose mothers treated with SSRI, analyzing the data of 51 404 children from the Norwegian cohort study of mothers and children, investigating the effects of the use of SSRI for the development of motor skills at the age of 3.
